    <stitle>CAB: 5000i AND 9000i CONVENTIONAL - ADJUSTMENTS - CAB SQUARING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x16021201" svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CAB SQUARING</title>
        <para>Cab squaring is the centering and perpendicular positioning of the cab structure to the frame. The cab
            must be squared whenever the cab has been removed from the chassis for repair, or if a new cab is being
            mounted.
        </para>
        <para>The cab must be properly squared to the frame as this adjustment will affect the relationship between the
            cab, hood and sleeper box. Improper squaring may result in unacceptable appearance and interference between
            the above units. Be sure the chassis is on a level surface before squaring.
        </para>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f16021166">Figure 166</hotlnk>
            for Items in parentheses.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Center cab (Item 1) on frame rail (Item 4) by using dimension (Item A) from cab cowl (Item
                5) to frame rail.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f16021166" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G16021e6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="208px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 166. Cab Front Mounting Dimension</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>A. 20 INCHES (508 mm)</callout1>
                <callout1>1. CAB</callout1>
                <callout1>2. CAB FRONT MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>3. CAB FRONT MOUNTING RETAINER</callout1>
                <callout1>4. FRAME RAIL</callout1>
                <callout1>5. CAB COWL LINE</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f16021167">Figure 167</hotlnk>
            for Items in parentheses.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Adjust cab to make cowl and back panel parallel and perpendicular to the frame. Add or
                remove shims (Item 2) between crossmember (Item 3) and cab lower rear mounting bracket (Item 1).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f16021167" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G16021e7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="208px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 167. Cab Rear Mounting</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. LOWER REAR MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SHIMS</callout1>
                <callout1>3. CROSSMEMBER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
